A function can be passed as an argument to a function
A function can be returned as values from another function

function greet(name){
    console.log(`Hello! ${name}`);
}

function greetYadhu(greetfn){
    const name = "Yadhu";
    greetfn(name);
}

greetYadhu(greet);


here greet is a callback function
and greetyadhu is the higher order function
....................................................................

Callback:
    A function passed as an argument to another function

Types of CallBacks:
    Synchronous:
        Callbacks executed immediately 
    Asynchronous:
        Resume code after an Asynchronous operation
        

